The present volume, product of a conference held in November 2011 at the University of Wrocaw,
in cooperation with Helmut-Schmidt University (Hamburg), is an interdisciplinary foray into Alexanders
short
stay
in
Egypt
and
his
legacy
in
Egyptian
culture.
Consisting
of
twenty-two
contributions

(excluding
the
